<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-1258 </DOCNO><TEXT>H.R. 2818 exempts qualifying small power production facilities of notmore than 80 megawatts that use solar energy from: (a) the Federal PowerAct (FPA); (b) the Public Utility Holding Company Act (PUHCA); and (c)most state laws and regulations governing electric utilities. Currentlaw and regulations exempt qualifying small power production facilitiesof not more than 30 megawatts that use solar energy from applicationof the above laws; H.R. 2818, accordingly, raises that ceiling from 30to 80 megawatts. The Committee on Energy and Commerce considered H.R.2818, reported favorably on it, and recommended the bill as amended bepassed.</TEXT></DOC>